      "side": 1,
      "message": "Wi-Fi hotspots in Android usually use dynamic BSSIDs (MAC addresses) that is constantly randomized. However, their SSIDs (the name that will show up in available networks) are not randomized and stay the same without manual modification. Therefore, if someone can identify and detect your hotspot SSID, they may be able to locate you and track your location pattern.",
